RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 84. Starter Allowance Purse 9500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $3,500 OR LESS SINCE MAY 27, 2022 AND WHICH HAVE NOT WON A STARTER ALLOWANCE RACE AT EMERALD DOWNS IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since December 27, 2022 Allowed 3 lbs. (Maiden Races, Claiming Races And Starters Races For $3,200 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUMMEROFTHESAMURAI saved ground early while being reserved off the pace, angled out 4-wide nearing the quarter pole and finished strongly to be in in the final sixteenth to win going away. JANERO ROSE saved ground stalking the pace, came three-wide into the stretch and finished strongly. LOW DOSE opened a clear early lead, saved ground setting the pace into deep stretch and held on well for the show when headed. CONFIDENCE BUILDER hopped in the air at the start to get away behind the field, then saved ground while being unhurried and was gaining slightly late. PARTY POLICE was allowed to settle in stride, came five-wide into the stretch but lacked a rally.

ENTRY.OWNER: Petroff Carl Minardo Dan and Nakagawa Russ

ENTRY.NAME: Confidence Builder
ENTRY.OWNER: Martinez David B and Hulk Russell
ENTRY.COMMENT: hopped start, unhurried, rail trip, late gain

ENTRY.NAME: Janero Rose
ENTRY.OWNER: Purple Rose Ranch and Stapley Brent

ENTRY.NAME: Low Dose
ENTRY.OWNER: Juan Pablo Silva Jr Racing Stable
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, saved ground, held show

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 65. Claiming Purse 9000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEVIL'S OFF DUTY was bumped at the start by Northern Blend, then moved up to take the early lead, saved ground setting the pace while increasing his advantage and won with something left. DANNY ZUKO prompted the pace while racing two-wide, was no match for the winner but finished well for the place. HADLEES HONOR was allowed to settle in stride, came three-wide into the stretch but lacked a rally. THIRSTY KISS dropped back early and failed to be a factor. NORTHERN BLEND broke out to bump Devil's Off Duty, then saved ground to the stretch while being forwardly placed and drifted out during the drive while tiring.

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out, bumped, forwardly placed, tired

ENTRY.OWNER: Elison Kenneth and Elison Vicky Jo

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Claiming Purse 16500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LANGSTON ROAD saved ground setting the pace and gradually increased his advantage. UNCLE PETE settled in stride early, angled out to be three-wide nearing the quarter pole and finished strongly for the place. TIME 'ER TOO prompted the issue while racing two-wide and held on for the show in a steady effort. WITHEE raced three-wide on the turn, came four-wide into the stretch and went evenly. THEUNTOUCHABLEONE raced along the outside of Withee and lacked a rally. QUALITY GRANDSON lacked early speed and failed to menace. ROYAL CANDY was off a step slow, then ducked in behind horses shortly after the start, steadied in tight nearing the seven-sixteenths pole, recovered to be forwardly placed to the stretch and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 77. Maiden Special Weight Purse 24000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TABLE BAY was forwardly placed early racing along the inside, rallied three-wide nearing the quarter pole, caught J C's a Legend nearing the sixteenth pole, was bumped by that one late and prevailed narrowly in a stiff drive. J C'S A LEGEND prompted the early pace while two-wide, took the lead from Amara Mike entering the stretch, came out late to bump the winner and just missed. SUPERMAX was prominent early while racing between horses on the turn and finished in a mild rally. AMARA MIKE saved ground setting the pace to the stretch and weakened. MANGIA PANE dropped back early, then saved ground and improved his position. ALL THE KING'S MEN was forwardly placed to the stretch while three-wide and tired. THE GOLDEN EGG was unhurried early, came five-wide into the stretch and failed to threaten. TAVERNELLE was off a step slow, raced three-wide and failed to menace. THE SREWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE STRETCH RUN, BUT AFTER VIEWING THE FILMS, MADE NO CHANGE IN THE ORDER OF FINISH.

ENTRY.NAME: Table Bay
ENTRY.COMMENT: forwardly placed, 3-w 1/4, caught leader 1/16, bumped, prevailed

ENTRY.NAME: J C's a Legend
ENTRY.OWNER: Two Putts for the Win Lucarelli Racing Corp and Bresko Aaron
ENTRY.COMMENT: prompted 2-wide, led entering, came out late, bumped, missed

ENTRY.OWNER: Essex Charles D and Crawford Joe

ENTRY.NAME: Mangia Pane
ENTRY.OWNER: Di Pietro, Luigi and DiPietro, Diana

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 90. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 25000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $10,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $30,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $30,000 (Maiden Races, Claiming Races And Starters Races Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OUR LYLA GRACE was reserved off the early pace, rallied five-wide the final quarter, led nearing the eighth pole and gradually drew clear. CAUSE SHE'S A LADY prompted the issue while racing three-wide and finished well for the place in a steady effort. MISS BELLA vied for the early lead while two-wide and held on well during the drive for the show. BRILLIANT BIRD vied for the lead to the stretch from along the inside and weakened late. PRESKITT was allowed to settle in stride, moved up six-wide nearing the quarter pole but lacked a rally. EMERALD SEA broke in the air to get away behind the field and failed to menace.

ENTRY.NAME: Emerald Sea
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in air, unhurried, no menace

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 80. Allowance Purse 22000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 3 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROYAL HALO vied for the early lead with Mister Midas from along the inside, shook that one off leaving the quarter pole and increased his advantage. MISTER MIDAS vied for the lead from the outside, was no match for the winner but held on well for the place. DESHAMBEAU was forwardly placed while racing three-wide and finished in a mild rally. ICE TOWER saved ground while being allowed to settle in stretch and went evenly late. BEAU MISCHIEF settled in the middle of the pack, was five-wide nearing the quarter pole and failed to threaten. SECRET SAGA was prominently placed early while racing four-wide but lacked a response when asked. MISTER MAFIOSO was off a step slow and failed to threaten.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 85. Allowance Purse 24000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR WASHINGTON BREDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 3 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAX CODE saved ground stalking the pace, slipped through along the inside to take the lead nearing the three-sixteenths pole, opened clear and maintained a safe advantage. NAVAL ESCORT was allowed to settle in stride while racing three-wide on the turn, came five-wide into the stretch and finished strongly. FIREWALKER was unhurried early, came six-wide into the stretch and finished in a mild rally. PESO settled in mid pack while racing two-wide and lacked a late response. NAPOLETANO saved ground and improved his position. MIDNIGHT MOJO dropped back early, came three-wide into the stretch, split rivals during the drive and failed to threaten. TIG vied for the lead with Prime Example from along the inside, drifted out leaving the quarter pole and tired. PRIME EXAMPLE vied for the lead from along the outside to the stretch and gave way.
